Syrian-Caramanian Line. Port Said, Jaffa, Beyrout,
                        Tripoli, Alexandretta, Mersina, Febr. 18;
                            March 4, 18 ; April 1. 15, 29 ; May 13, 27 ;
                            June 10, 24.

6th—On being admitted, candidates must sign an engagement that they will work
                        either in Upper or Lower Egypt during the whole or part of their service, as
                        may be ordered by the Administration;

7th—Pupils will receive P.T. 7 per day each during the period allowed for
                        studying telegraphy and will receive higher pay when they have the telegraph
                        certificate when they will be absorbed in the staff of the stations;

8th—If during the period of apprenticeship pupils do not give satisfaction,
                        they will be dismissed; and will not have the right to any claim
                        whatever;
